:{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Hi, I noticed that you can't set a default value in the set_value function if you load the Form_validation with set_rules called for the input. I've diagnosed the problem and devised a fix below:\n\ncontroller:\n\n{{{\n# !php\n\n$this->load->library('form_validation');\n\n// when the following is called, the library sets `$this->_field_data[$field]['postdata']` field as NULL\n$this->form_validation->set_rules('title', 'Title', 'required');\n}}}\n\nview:\n\n{{{\n# !php\n\n// the set_value function in the form_validation library detects that `$this->_field_data[$field]` exists and returns `$this->_field_data[$field]['postdata']`, ignoring the default value set by me\necho set_value('title', 'my default value here'); // outputs nothing\n}}}\n\nhere's the fix:\nfind this line\n\n{{{\n# !php\n\n```\nfunction set_value($field = '', $default = '')\n{\n    if ( ! isset($this->_field_data[$field]))\n    {\n        return $default;\n    }\n\n    ...\n```\n\n}}}\n\nand replace it with\n{{{\n# !php\n\n```\nfunction set_value($field = '', $default = '')\n{\n    if ( ! isset($this->_field_data[$field]) OR $this->_field_data[$field]['postdata'] === NULL)\n    {\n        return $default;\n    }\n\n    ...\n```\n\n}}}\n","closed_by":{"login":"narfbg","id":1058011,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwNTgwMTE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1058011?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg","html_url":"https://github.com/narfbg","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/u